Let $\mathbf{u} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}.$  The projection of $\mathbf{u}$ onto $\mathbf{v}$ is given by
\begin{align*} \text{proj}_{\mathbf{v}} \mathbf{u} &= \frac{\mathbf{u} \cdot \mathbf{v}}{\|\mathbf{v}\|^2} \mathbf{v} \\ &= \frac{\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}{\left\| \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \right\|^2} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\ &= \frac{(4)(2) + (5)(0)}{2^2 + 0^2} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\ &= \frac{8}{4} \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\ &= 2 \begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix} \\ &= \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}. \end{align*}

Final Answer: $\boxed{\begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 0 \end{pmatrix}}$
